  "title": "Facilities Engineer (M&E/Construction)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Provide support in organizing and overseeing day-to-day facility upkeep to keep project activities on track.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate project timelines and deliverables with clients, consultants, and subcontractors for timely completion.</li>\n  <li>Perform on-site inspections to monitor work progress, conduct quality checks, and provide feedback for improvements.</li>\n  <li>Support the preparation and submission of technical drawings and related project documentation.</li>\n  <li>Handle administrative duties linked to project activities and provide on-site support when necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Mechanical, Electrical Engineering, or equivalent</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience in the <strong>M&amp;E/Construction Industry.</strong></li>\n  <li>Advantageous to have relevant <strong>safety certifications.</strong></li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and under tight deadlines.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br>\nRegistration: R1326740</p>",
